Akzo Nobel Functional Chemicals LLC also complies with the Clean Air Act, Clean Water Act, Resource Conservation and Recovery Act, and various federal, state, and local rules.

The Five-Year Accident History

For the past five-year period, there have been four releases that could potentially have had an off-site impact.  Akzo Nobel Functional Chemicals LLC had a release of 3,150 pounds of phosphorus oxychloride in 1998, with no off-site injuries or environmental damage.  Akzo Nobel Functional Chemicals LLC had two releases of ethylene oxide during the past five-year period, both in 1999.  The largest release was 60 pounds, and the second release was 43 pounds.  Akzo Nobel Functional Chemicals LLC had a release of propylene oxide of 633 pounds in 1999.  There was no environmental damage and no one off-site was injured during any of these releases; however, as a precautionary measure, shelter in place was called during one of the 1999 ethylene oxide events.

